abstract:

Type annotations still not received that amount of popularity, that should. People still finding them hard and sometimes ambiguous to use. But if you start new project in Python in 2018 you should consider using type annotations in your code and this short talk describes why. I'll go over examples, where type annotations helped my team to create less complex code, and how using type annotations changing your mind for projecting & implementing features for your project.
---
full_description:

Type annotations still not received that amount of popularity, that should. People still finding them hard and sometimes ambiguous to use. But if you start new project in Python in 2018 you should consider using type annotations in your code and this short talk describes why.

I'll go over examples, where type annotations helped my team to create less complex code, and how using type annotations changing your mind for projecting & implementing features for your project.
